  "text": "[VIII] the Goldfeld-Quandt homoscedasticity test statistic GQm i concerned with equal variance σ 2 of the disturbance term U must satisfy the following inequality at a 100ω% significance level of an F test, if (i) it is considered that structural changes may have happened and affected σ 2 and (ii) the Goldfeld-Quandt test need be applied to maintain the null hypothesis H 0 : V(u t ) = σ 2 for all t (and covariance C(u t u s ) = 0 for all s = 1, 2, . . . , T but t = s) against the alternative hypothesis H 1 : V(u t ) = V(u s ) for at least one of pairs {t, s} [CITATION_1] )",
